LORE midgaard-clerk
FLAGS MIDGAARD CLERK
- Lantern Registry: maintains routes, names, and what other institutions prefer
  buried; Breach Tower floor believed to hold duplicate Unindexed Year ledgers
- Magistrate Ledgerhouse: civil law, documentation, petitions; most disputes
  settle before a magistrate sees them
- Three civic oaths (posted in every administrative office): "No ward unlit,
  no traveler uncounted." "No judgment hidden, no sentence unrecorded." "No
  levy taken that cannot be borne." All violated in practice.
- Continuity faction holds most senior clerk positions; Reckoning faction has
  been placing junior clerks in archival access roles for years
- Containment Era documents use different indexing than post-Ash-and-Iron
  records; finding anything from that period requires knowing the old system
- Petition process for non-citizens: arms declaration at Guard Command first,
  then residential notation at the Registry, then the relevant department
~
